A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 11 of Title 31 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 emergency medical services, so as to provide for the licensing and operation of emergency
3 organ transport vehicles as ambulance services; to provide for license application; to provide
4 for insurance coverage requirements; to require compliance with rules and regulations of the
5 Department of Public Health by such vehicles; to exempt emergency organ transport vehicles
6 from requirements relative to the Emergency Medical Systems Communications (EMSC)
7 Program and a medical adviser; to provide for the operation of such vehicles on public
8 roadways; to amend Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to motor
9 vehicles and traffic, so as to exempt emergency organ transport vehicles from those vehicles
10 required to obtain an emergency vehicle permit from the Department of Public Safety; to
11 revise and provide for definitions; to provide for a short title; to provide for related matters;
12 to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
14 SECTION 1.
15 This Act shall be known and may be cited as the "Georgia Transporting Life-Saving Organs
16 and Personnel Act."
