17 SECTION 2.
18 Chapter 11 of Title 31 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to emergency
19 medical services, is amended in Code Section 31-11-2, relating to definitions, by revising
20 paragraph (4) and by adding a new paragraph to read as follows:
21 "(4) 'Ambulance service' means:
22 (A) The providing of emergency care and transportation on the public streets and
23 highways of this state for a wounded, injured, sick, invalid, or incapacitated human
24 being to or from a place where medical or hospital care is furnished;
25 (B) The provision of any air ambulance service; or
26 (C) The provision of transportation services on the public streets and highways of this
27 state for the transport of necessary personnel, organs, tissue, or medical supplies to a
28 time-critical organ transplant procedure; or
29 (D) The provision of services specified in subparagraphs (A) and (B) of this
30 paragraph."
31 "(9.1) 'Emergency organ transplant vehicle' means a motor vehicle that is intended to be
32 used for the transport of necessary personnel, organs, tissue, or medical supplies to a
33 time-critical organ transplant procedure."
