40 SECTION 4.
41 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 31-11-7, relating to exercise of
42 emergency vehicle privileges by ambulance drivers, as follows:
43 "31-11-7.
44 (a) The driver of an ambulance on the public streets, highways, and private access roads
45 of this state, when responding to an emergency call or while transporting a patient, is shall
46 be authorized to operate the ambulance as an emergency vehicle pursuant to Code Section
47 40-6-6.
48 (b) The driver of an emergency organ transport vehicle on the public streets, highways,
49 and private access roads of this state, when transporting necessary personnel, organs,
50 tissue, or medical supplies to a time-critical organ transplant procedure, shall be authorized
51 to operate the emergency organ transport vehicle as an emergency vehicle pursuant to Code
52 Section 40-6-6."
