66 SECTION 6.
67 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 31-11-33, relating to insurance
68 coverage as condition of licensing, as follows:
69 "31-11-33.
70 (a) Every ambulance and emergency organ transport vehicle operated on the streets,
71 highways, and private access roads of this state by persons engaged in providing
72 ambulance service shall have insurance coverage issued by an insurance company licensed
73 to do business in this state providing at least the minimum coverage required for motor
74 vehicles under Chapter 34 of Title 33; provided, however, that in the case of ambulances
75 or emergency organ transport vehicles operated by the state, the coverage required shall be
76 the same coverage required for other state vehicles under Chapter 9 of Title 45. Every air
77 ambulance operated by persons engaged in providing air ambulance service in this state
78 shall have insurance coverage as described in Code Section 33-7-9.
79 (b) No ambulance or emergency organ transport vehicle shall be licensed nor shall any
80 license be renewed unless the ambulance or emergency organ transport vehicle has
81 insurance coverage in force as required by this Code section. A certificate of insurance
82 shall be submitted to the license officer for approval prior to the issuance or renewal of
83 each ambulance license and emergency organ transport vehicle license. Satisfactory
84 evidence that such insurance is at all times in force and effect shall be furnished to the
85 license officer, in such form as he or she may specify, by all licensees required to provide
86 such insurance under this Code section.
87 (c) This Code section shall apply to all ambulances and emergency organ transport
88 vehicles, whether privately operated or operated by any political subdivision of the state
89 or any municipality thereof.
90 (d) This Code section shall not apply to first responders, which do not transport patients,
91 operated by municipalities or counties that have not elected to waive their governmental
92 immunity by purchasing vehicle liability insurance pursuant to Code Section 33-24-51."
